1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,620
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:32,220
♫I never know what love is like♫

7
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:37,020
♫All my life, never once have I experienced it♫

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,340
♫No one to take that place in my heart♫

9
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:47,580
♫But now that I’ve met you, my heart begins to glow♫

10
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:52,340
♫What feeling is this? Why is my heart fluttering?♫

11
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,460
♫And I just can’t control it.♫

12
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,300
♫What happened to my heart right now?♫

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,140
♫I can’t control it when you’re around♫

14
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:10,300
♫This heart…it stops at you♫

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,340
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

16
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,740
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

17
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,380
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

18
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,460
♫ From dusk till dawn, you’re never far from my sight♫

19
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:30,860
♫ Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

20
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:34,340
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

21
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:40,500
♫ Is this really happening ? I really want to know ♫

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,740
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:46,420
[Waves of Deception]
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

24
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:50,300
[Previously]
Boss trusted me to take care of this event.

25
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:54,100
But I failed to protect the guests and our hotel’s reputation.

26
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,500
This noodle is quite good.

27
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:59,740
That means you’re opening up to a plain and useless thing.

28
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:01,460
It’s because you made them.

29
00:02:01,460 --> 00:02:03,780
Tell Dad to tell that doctor Trai…

30
00:02:03,780 --> 00:02:06,060
that Miss Chonlada won’t have time for anyone.

31
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:08,220
Is this the girl Lom said is your girlfriend?

32
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:09,979
Our relationship is strictly professional.

33
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:12,020
Nothing more than that.

34
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:13,940
Please don’t stoop so low, Pat.

35
00:02:13,940 --> 00:02:18,380
The more you say it, the more I’m sure how much that woman means to you.

36
00:02:18,380 --> 00:02:21,220
Chonlada suddenly gave me a cold shoulder.

37
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:23,900
Big Boss said an important guest

38
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,500
will come for dinner tonight.

39
00:02:25,940 --> 00:02:27,220
- See you tomorrow.
- Boss.

40
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:32,900
Dad!

41
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,180
Hey!

42
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:40,180
Why do you have to be so loud? I lost now.

43
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:42,930
Boss, I thought you said you had work to do.

44
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:48,160
When you said you already have a plan, is it with my dad?

45
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:54,860
Well, since you want to invite her but don’t have the courage to do it;

46
00:02:55,540 --> 00:02:57,500
I’m doing the honours instead.

47
00:03:03,860 --> 00:03:07,180
Now that we're all here, let’s have dinner then.

48
00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:08,820
Come, Lada. Let’s eat.

49
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,360
Yes.

50
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:15,020
- Let’s go.
- Yes.

51
00:03:30,860 --> 00:03:35,220
Your chance has come. Don’t let it slip away. You can do it!

52
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:49,660
All right, the food is ready. Enjoy your meal.

53
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,339
Is the food at my house delicious?

54
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,740
It’s wonderful.

55
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:29,660
Then, you must come join us more often.

56
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:33,620
If Nam is too afraid to invite you here, I’ll do it instead.

57
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:39,960
Dad, don’t say that. You’re making her feel uncomfortable.

58
00:04:41,159 --> 00:04:42,800
I don’t think so.

59
00:04:43,460 --> 00:04:47,220
She’d rather feel uncomfortable because you ignore her.

60
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:51,100
All you do is work and hardly have time for her.

61
00:04:54,730 --> 00:04:58,580
Hey, don’t just sit there like a log. Why don’t you serve her the fish?

62
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:00,020
I don’t think she can reach it.

63
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,220
Let me do it for you.

64
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:14,940
It’s okay. I can take care of myself.

65
00:05:24,130 --> 00:05:26,820
Geez, don’t make it so obvious.

66
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,700
Sir, the flowers you’ve ordered are here.

67
00:05:33,159 --> 00:05:38,700
That’s right, Nam! Didn’t you order them for Lada?

68
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,220
Give them to her.

69
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,860
They’re for you.

70
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,300
I’m sorry about my dad earlier.

71
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,380
It was all his plan, wasn’t it?

72
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,980
I’ll let it slide then.

73
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:27,260
You shouldn’t take it seriously too.

74
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,020
I can’t not take it seriously.

75
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:39,940
[Nam]: How will this smart watch help me know how Chonlada feels about me?

76
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:46,460
Whenever she’s near, is your heart beating fast?

77
00:07:49,330 --> 00:07:50,220
So?

78
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,260
It is, right?

79
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:56,659
That’s because you’re getting nervous and shy.

80
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,100
You can’t control yourself and don’t know what to do

81
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:04,340
because you have feelings for her.

82
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:09,060
So?

83
00:08:10,060 --> 00:08:15,580
Just wait and see if her heart will also feel the same as you do.

84
00:08:30,460 --> 00:08:33,140
[Phone ringing]

85
00:08:46,330 --> 00:08:50,300
Please drive home safely, Boss. I’ll see you later.

86
00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:52,220
Hold on.

87
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:02,180
Can I have the flowers back?

88
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:08,360
I was about to return them anyway.

89
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:14,900
I’m going to throw them away.

90
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,500
Why would you do that?

91
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:31,580
I’ll pick you up tomorrow morning. See you then.

92
00:09:33,060 --> 00:09:33,820
What?

93
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:32,560
Why are you giving me flowers?

94
00:11:33,530 --> 00:11:35,980
The one you got yesterday wasn't from me.

95
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:38,460
So, I’m bringing you one today.

96
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:45,600
Why a pink tulip?

97
00:11:46,460 --> 00:11:47,300
Because you like it.

98
00:11:51,730 --> 00:11:53,540
How did you know?

99
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:03,420
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it?♫

100
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:06,460
♫ When my heart starts to waver♫

101
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:11,140
♫ Like a stream of water slowly pouring over my heart♫

102
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:14,300
♫ From dusk till dawn, all I see is you♫

103
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:18,860
♫Or is this love? Are you that someone...♫

104
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:22,220
♫ ...who’s destined to be with me?♫

105
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:28,260
♫ Is this really happening? I really want to know ♫

106
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:33,460
♫‘Cos you now hold a special place in my heart♫

107
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:39,900
Chonlada! Chonlada! Please wait.

108
00:12:48,460 --> 00:12:52,460
I can't accept it, Boss. People might see us.

109
00:12:55,130 --> 00:12:57,460
Why don’t you want them to see us?

110
00:12:58,860 --> 00:13:01,220
Have you forgotten about the rumour?

111
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:06,060
I already told you. I don’t care about that rumour anymore.

112
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,700
That’s because you’re not an employee.

113
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:11,780
You have nothing to worry about. But I do.

114
00:13:12,730 --> 00:13:15,700
Every day when they look at me with those suspicious eyes,

115
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:18,100
I keep worrying whether they’d think I’m trying to seduce you.

116
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:26,930
So, you’ve been avoiding me all this time just because you care what they’d think about us?

117
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:36,460
I’ll make everything clear to them then.

118
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:44,360
What do you mean?

119
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:51,940
If you’re afraid that they’d think you have a hidden agenda for trying to get close to me,

120
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:55,020
I’ll be the one to pursue you instead.

121
00:13:55,420 --> 00:13:59,940
I’ll make them know how I feel about you, and why I like you.

122
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:07,300
And I promise to never mix business with our relationship.

123
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:19,860
[Incoming message]

124
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,060
But I don't have feelings for you.

125
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:56,330
Then, why aren’t you wearing that smart watch I gave you?

126
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,300
I forgot.

127
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:10,140
Really? Or are you afraid that I’ll know you also feel the same as I do.

128
00:15:10,660 --> 00:15:14,460
No. I’m not wearing it because I don’t like being forced.

129
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:18,860
Just like how you’re forcing me to accept your flowers when I don’t want to.

130
00:15:20,930 --> 00:15:22,660
I chose to work here,

131
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:26,930
because I want to prove to my family that a daughter like me can also make them proud.

132
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:29,730
I admire you and your talent.

133
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:37,540
But if that admiration has led you to misunderstand how I feel, I’m really sorry.

134
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:47,740
I look up to you because you’re talented.

135
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:52,360
That’s all I feel about you, Boss.

136
00:15:57,730 --> 00:16:00,460
From now on, let’s strictly keep it professional like how we should be.

137
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:04,420
Please don’t make me feel any more uncomfortable.

138
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:07,260
I’m begging you.

139
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:43,960
Miss Preem, please don’t forget to send me the meeting report of the department heads.

140
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:45,760
Yes, Boss.

141
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:37,400
This means you’re opening up to something plain and useless.

142
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:43,820
It’s because you made them.

143
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:05,540
[Apo]: Hello, Miss Chonlada.

144
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,460
[Chonlada]: How did you get my LINE ID?

145
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:41,580
[Apo]: From Miss Preem. I don’t want to call. I’m afraid it might bother you.

146
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:00,860
[Apo]: I just want to apologise for today.

147
00:20:02,060 --> 00:20:05,820
[Apo]: I’ll only be your boss from now on. Nothing more.

148
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:30,900
[Chonlada typing]

149
00:20:33,660 --> 00:20:38,940
It’s not what you think, Boss. Actually, I also feel…

150
00:20:43,540 --> 00:20:50,220
[Phone ringing]

151
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:53,360
Yes, Pat?

152
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:56,100
I already know what Dad is going to do to my hotel.

153
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:58,740
This is all because you refused to help me, Lada.

154
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:02,200
Please calm down. Let me explain first.

155
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:05,420
The Watin Group is going to have a big private event for their customers.

156
00:21:05,420 --> 00:21:07,860
I want it ruined, Lada. I want it ruined!

157
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:09,740
It wouldn't do us any good, Pat.

158
00:21:10,730 --> 00:21:13,860
Fine, I’ll do it then.

159
00:21:16,060 --> 00:21:17,500
Pat? Pat!

160
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:36,940
This is a private event arranged for our exclusive customers who work in the media industry.

161
00:21:36,940 --> 00:21:39,620
It is our chance to restore the reputation of our hotel.

162
00:21:39,620 --> 00:21:40,860
Please do your best, everyone.

163
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:41,960
Miss Preem.

164
00:21:44,860 --> 00:21:48,100
All the 25 guests who will attend the event are now here.

165
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:50,180
They’re waiting in the lobby.

166
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:51,580
Okay, good.

167
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:55,220
Mr. Boy, can you recheck everything with the kitchen team again?

168
00:21:55,220 --> 00:21:59,420
Miss Wadee, please go welcome the guests and confirm the list of those who would stay at the resort.

169
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:02,020
Make sure to prepare some extra rooms, just in case.

170
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:03,100
Sure, Miss Preem.

171
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:14,060
Well then, I’ll go check out the outdoor zone.

172
00:22:14,380 --> 00:22:18,300
It’s pretty cloudy today. Hopefully, it won’t rain.

173
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:23,500
I hope so too. It’s an outdoor event. We’ll surely have problems  if it rains.

174
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,900
I’m afraid Boss is still in the meeting.

175
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:30,020
How about this? While I’m checking out the outdoor zone,

176
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:32,580
I’ll stop by the banquet room and tell them to be prepared.

177
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:36,340
So that we can have a backup plan and move the guests inside in case of emergency.

178
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:40,530
Let’s do that. I’ll let Boss know once she’s done with the meeting.

179
00:22:40,930 --> 00:22:41,700
Okay.

180
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:00,420
Excuse me, sir?

181
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:03,100
Sir!

182
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:06,820
Sir!

183
00:23:07,580 --> 00:23:08,420
Sir!

184
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:09,700
Please stop!

185
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:11,700
Stop!

186
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:33,260
[Pheempat]: The Watin Group is going to have a big private event for their customers.

187
00:23:33,530 --> 00:23:35,980
[Pheempat]: I want it ruined, Lada. I want it ruined!

188
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:38,140
[Thundering]

189
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:41,780
Miss Lada! Miss Lada!

190
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:42,700
Miss Preem.

191
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:48,900
I just told Boss. She told me to get you to arrange the event inside.

192
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:53,180
I’ve checked the climate. The storm is coming.

193
00:23:54,340 --> 00:23:56,900
Where is Boss now?

194
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:59,220
She said she has to take care of something in the garden first.

195
00:23:59,220 --> 00:24:01,540
Then she’ll go see us at the banquet room.

196
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:26,060
Boss! Boss, can you hear me? Boss! Boss!

197
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:28,140
Chonlada!

198
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,500
Chonlada!

199
00:24:34,180 --> 00:24:35,620
Chonlada!

200
00:24:37,330 --> 00:24:38,130
Chonlada!

201
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:39,530
Boss!

202
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:41,700
Boss!

203
00:24:42,330 --> 00:24:45,620
Can you hear me, Boss? Boss!

204
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:47,600
Boss!

205
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:50,060
Chonlada!

206
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:55,600
Chonlada!

207
00:25:00,940 --> 00:25:01,860
Boss!

208
00:25:13,100 --> 00:25:14,260
Boss, look out!

209
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:35,020
Boss! Are you okay, Boss? Why did you come here?

210
00:25:36,730 --> 00:25:40,330
Miss Preem said you’re here. It’s raining so I’m worried about you.

211
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:42,140
Please don’t do this, Boss.

212
00:25:42,620 --> 00:25:44,980
The more you care about me, the more danger you’re in.

213
00:25:45,860 --> 00:25:48,180
You don’t know how scared I am.

214
00:25:51,930 --> 00:25:54,300
I don’t know what it is that you fear,

215
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:57,260
or why you think someone is going to hurt me.

216
00:25:58,940 --> 00:26:03,300
But if you do care about me, please don’t leave me.

217
00:26:15,060 --> 00:26:17,930
I can’t see you as an assistant anymore, Chonlada.

218
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:24,740
No matter what happens, I will never leave you.

219
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,540
We’ll go through it together.

220
00:28:07,730 --> 00:28:10,140
This is my private guesthouse.

221
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:12,860
You can go shower first.

222
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:18,580
The PJ’s are there. I have them just in case when I stay over.

223
00:28:22,700 --> 00:28:27,540
Actually, I can walk back like this and change into a new uniform in the toilet.

224
00:28:27,780 --> 00:28:30,620
That way, I can help Miss Preem take care of the guests at the event too.

225
00:28:33,330 --> 00:28:35,100
Can’t you see it’s raining?

226
00:28:37,900 --> 00:28:40,260
You’ll get sick if you keep walking in the rain.

227
00:28:41,530 --> 00:28:44,460
Don’t worry, I take vitamin supplements every day.

228
00:28:49,730 --> 00:28:51,740
See? What did I just tell you?

229
00:28:57,220 --> 00:29:01,900
Boss, I’ll…Oh!

230
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:07,660
I’m so sorry, Boss. I didn’t mean it. I’m sorry.

231
00:29:09,980 --> 00:29:14,460
Has anyone ever told you that you’d look much prettier if you’re less stubborn?

232
00:29:15,930 --> 00:29:16,900
I’m sorry.

233
00:29:17,300 --> 00:29:20,460
I promise my clumsiness will never affect my work.

234
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,060
I’ll be more careful in the future.

235
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:28,220
I’m not complaining or anything.

236
00:29:28,660 --> 00:29:30,220
Stop apologising.

237
00:29:31,300 --> 00:29:34,140
Caring about you is also something personal.

238
00:29:37,500 --> 00:29:38,780
Just go shower.

239
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:42,860
I’ll wait outside so that you won’t feel awkward.

240
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:46,540
It’s okay. You can wait here.

241
00:29:46,540 --> 00:29:47,740
I won’t take long.

242
00:29:51,130 --> 00:29:54,620
Are you sure you want me to stay?

243
00:30:04,860 --> 00:30:08,060
So, I’ll let you know when I’m done.

244
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:14,980
I still haven’t told you where the toiletries are.

245
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:19,580
I can shout to ask.

246
00:30:55,860 --> 00:30:57,580
[Phone ringing]

247
00:31:25,930 --> 00:31:26,730
Did you find anything?

248
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:30,860
About that man you find suspicious, I’ve looked into him.

249
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:36,820
Does anyone know I’ve asked you to do this?

250
00:31:38,930 --> 00:31:40,560
Hey, I’m the resort owner’s sister.

251
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:42,820
Who would dare suspect me?

252
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:47,940
I checked the CCTV cameras and the name list of all employees.

253
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:50,860
He isn’t the staff here.

254
00:31:52,260 --> 00:31:54,420
So, like Chef Ian’s event,

255
00:31:55,130 --> 00:31:57,220
it wasn’t an accident, was it?

256
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:01,340
This matter is not complicated at all.

257
00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:06,860
And I’m sure you’ve already figured out who’s behind this.

258
00:32:07,260 --> 00:32:10,500
Can you look more into this matter for me?

259
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:14,500
Find out if there’s still any staff who secretly works for the Wachara Group.

260
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:16,160
Sure.

261
00:33:33,620 --> 00:33:35,100
[Glass shattering]

262
00:33:45,380 --> 00:33:46,420
Boss!

263
00:33:46,860 --> 00:33:49,380
I wasn’t being clumsy.

264
00:33:49,380 --> 00:33:53,300
I just wanted to check if the rain had stopped.

265
00:33:54,130 --> 00:33:57,780
I was about to go inside but my hand knocked it over.

266
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:06,220
Are you saying that it’s my fault because I broke your glasses?

267
00:34:07,730 --> 00:34:08,760
I was only explaining.

268
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:14,530
Don’t worry, I intend to pay for your glasses anyway.

269
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:17,300
Your hands might get hurt.

270
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:23,699
If you really want to take responsibility,

271
00:34:24,820 --> 00:34:26,980
you don’t need to pay me anything.

272
00:34:33,530 --> 00:34:34,980
Please sleep here tonight.

273
00:34:55,260 --> 00:34:58,180
[Thundering]

274
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:19,220
Wait. Where are you going?

275
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:25,140
Just because I let you kiss me doesn’t mean you can do anything to me.

276
00:35:25,140 --> 00:35:27,580
It’s a no no, Boss. You’ve made the wrong move.

277
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:32,300
What are you thinking?

278
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:35,260
Well, you told me to sleep here with you.

279
00:35:35,260 --> 00:35:37,260
What should I think?

280
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:43,220
The reason I said that is because…Look.

281
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:45,940
It’s still raining.

282
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:48,330
Also, Miss Preem just called and told us,

283
00:35:48,500 --> 00:35:51,740
to stay inside because another storm is coming.

284
00:35:53,530 --> 00:35:55,500
Why didn’t you say it earlier?

285
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:59,530
You didn’t even wait to hear it.

286
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:04,780
You sleep here then.

287
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:08,380
I’ll go sleep at my dad’s place.

288
00:36:16,530 --> 00:36:17,820
Be careful.

289
00:36:17,820 --> 00:36:21,060
You’re not wearing glasses now. How can you drive?

290
00:36:21,060 --> 00:36:22,700
Will you even see anything?

291
00:36:25,260 --> 00:36:27,140
But you won’t let me sleep here.

292
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:32,400
If you just want to sleep, that’s fine. No problem.

293
00:36:34,100 --> 00:36:37,300
What if it’s not just a sleep?

294
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:48,020
Why don’t you go shower?

295
00:36:48,020 --> 00:36:49,700
Otherwise, you might catch a cold.

296
00:37:41,460 --> 00:37:44,760
Boss, I told you to sleep in bed, not on the couch.

297
00:37:47,100 --> 00:37:49,260
I’m too tired to argue with you.

298
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,700
Good night then.

299
00:37:51,730 --> 00:37:54,980
Wait. Get up, Boss.

300
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:55,660
No.

301
00:37:55,660 --> 00:37:57,020
- Boss!
- Chonlada.

302
00:37:58,600 --> 00:37:59,400
Get up.

303
00:38:25,600 --> 00:38:29,700
Can I have the smart watch I gave you back?

304
00:38:30,930 --> 00:38:31,800
Why?

305
00:38:33,780 --> 00:38:38,620
Because right now, I think your heart and mine,

306
00:38:39,340 --> 00:38:41,780
are already beating as one.

307
00:38:45,820 --> 00:38:47,420
Boss.

308
00:38:50,330 --> 00:38:55,860
If you want to take responsibility for breaking my glasses, I don’t want you to pay me anything.

309
00:38:57,930 --> 00:39:02,460
All I want is for you to stay by my side

310
00:39:06,300 --> 00:39:07,700
and never let go of my hands.

311
00:39:10,600 --> 00:39:13,340
But I’m so clumsy.

312
00:39:14,860 --> 00:39:17,060
Those who stay near me always get hurt.

313
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,980
I don’t want you to cause you any trouble.

314
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:25,820
I’m not afraid, as long as I have you by my side.

315
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:31,060
Please be my glasses, Chonlada.

316
00:39:35,180 --> 00:39:36,500
Boss.

317
00:39:45,130 --> 00:39:47,340
But the couch is too small.

318
00:39:47,340 --> 00:39:49,220
There isn’t enough room for both of us.

319
00:40:14,860 --> 00:40:16,620
Let’s sleep on the floor then.

320
00:40:18,460 --> 00:40:22,420
Just like when we had noodles in your room.

321
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:35,780
Get some sleep.

322
00:40:36,330 --> 00:40:37,740
Let’s deal with it tomorrow.

323
00:40:52,730 --> 00:40:54,580
My dad used to tell me

324
00:40:56,530 --> 00:40:58,700
that no matter what tomorrow will bring,

325
00:40:59,340 --> 00:41:05,020
as long as right now we’re happy with something;

326
00:41:06,500 --> 00:41:08,300
we should make the best of it

327
00:41:10,130 --> 00:41:15,700
and let tomorrow be a matter of the future.

328
00:43:01,140 --> 00:43:04,580
[No need to fix them. No matter how many you’ll have, I’ll always be your glasses, Boss.]

329
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:38,060
Eat more. You’re so light I thought I was carrying a kitten.

330
00:45:28,180 --> 00:45:31,420
Boss, are you sure you won’t go to the hospital?

331
00:45:32,020 --> 00:45:35,740
I’m fine. It’ll get better after drinking some warm water. Thanks a lot.

332
00:45:39,140 --> 00:45:41,380
Por, please get me a glass of warm water.

333
00:45:42,780 --> 00:45:48,020
It’s my fault that you had to stay out in the rain and catch a cold.

334
00:45:50,260 --> 00:45:53,340
It’s not your fault. I just didn’t get enough sleep lately.

335
00:46:00,180 --> 00:46:02,260
You’re burning up.

336
00:46:02,460 --> 00:46:07,420
If you don’t get some rest, I’m afraid you’ll end up taking a long sick leave.

337
00:46:09,060 --> 00:46:10,780
I can’t rest now.

338
00:46:16,260 --> 00:46:23,020
If you agree to take some rest, I’ll look after you until you’re feeling well.

339
00:46:41,380 --> 00:46:45,820
I thought you said you’d rest. Does ‘rest’ mean working for you?

340
00:46:50,380 --> 00:46:51,380
What porridge is it?

341
00:46:53,740 --> 00:46:59,020
If you finish it and take your pills afterward, I’ll give you a reward.

342
00:47:01,380 --> 00:47:04,620
I’m not a kid. You can’t lure me with a gift.

343
00:47:05,100 --> 00:47:10,020
So, you don’t want a gift from me?

344
00:47:31,380 --> 00:47:32,980
Eat the pork too.

345
00:47:53,500 --> 00:47:54,780
Take your pills too.

346
00:47:56,340 --> 00:47:57,740
Or do you want me to feed you?

347
00:48:21,500 --> 00:48:23,260
You’re a good girl.

348
00:49:07,940 --> 00:49:13,340
When I was young and fell sick, I hardly had an appetite.

349
00:49:13,340 --> 00:49:19,660
But when my mum knew I love flowers, she used them to cook porridge for me.

350
00:49:19,660 --> 00:49:22,660
So that I could eat something. I even finished it all.

351
00:49:25,300 --> 00:49:28,580
But since I’m not good at cooking, I decided to…

352
00:49:38,940 --> 00:49:41,460
buy you a flower instead.

353
00:49:55,740 --> 00:49:57,340
I like sunflowers.

354
00:49:59,140 --> 00:50:04,260
Do you really mean it, or did you just say it to please me?

355
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:07,700
I really mean it.

356
00:50:15,740 --> 00:50:17,660
That you like sunflowers?

357
00:50:22,140 --> 00:50:23,580
Have you always liked them?

358
00:50:24,740 --> 00:50:25,540
Only recently.

359
00:50:30,900 --> 00:50:36,220
But I’m going to like them forever because you gave it to me.

360
00:50:46,780 --> 00:50:49,340
Please get some rest so that you’ll recover soon, Boss.

361
00:50:50,900 --> 00:50:54,860
Hold on. When is your birthday?

362
00:51:23,100 --> 00:51:28,500
My dad used to tell me that no matter what tomorrow will bring,

363
00:51:30,060 --> 00:51:39,060
as long as right now we’re happy with something; we should make the best of it

364
00:51:40,820 --> 00:51:46,660
and let tomorrow be a matter of the future.

365
00:52:33,740 --> 00:52:34,540
Pat!

366
00:52:35,860 --> 00:52:38,020
I know you’re somewhere around here.

367
00:52:38,740 --> 00:52:40,940
You can threaten me all you like but I won’t be afraid anymore.

368
00:52:43,260 --> 00:52:45,180
I’m going to tell Miss Apo everything.

369
00:52:46,300 --> 00:52:48,020
Show your face if you’re man enough.

370
00:52:52,900 --> 00:52:55,060
[Phone ringing]

371
00:52:57,540 --> 00:52:58,780
Hello, Pat.

372
00:52:59,060 --> 00:53:00,740
Did you really mean it?

373
00:53:03,340 --> 00:53:04,140
Pat.

374
00:53:05,260 --> 00:53:07,740
Do you really think she’d still accept you if you tell her the truth?

375
00:53:09,100 --> 00:53:10,100
Go on then.

376
00:53:10,180 --> 00:53:15,380
I also want to know what she’d say when she finds out you’re my sister.

377
00:53:16,660 --> 00:53:17,940
Go on, Chonlada.

378
00:53:20,060 --> 00:53:23,620
Hurry up and tell her. Go!

379
00:53:24,580 --> 00:53:26,860
Go! I said f***ing go!

380
00:53:34,340 --> 00:53:36,580
Boss!

381
00:53:39,340 --> 00:53:40,780
Where are you rushing to?

382
00:53:42,340 --> 00:53:44,540
Boss, what are you doing here? Why are you not resting?

383
00:53:49,180 --> 00:53:50,100
Is there something wrong?

384
00:53:51,660 --> 00:53:54,740
No, I’m just taking a walk.

385
00:53:56,540 --> 00:53:59,220
Are you hungry? What do you want to eat for dinner?

386
00:54:00,340 --> 00:54:02,980
I’m not hungry yet. Are you?

387
00:54:04,860 --> 00:54:06,740
Should we go eat somewhere by the beach?

388
00:54:08,580 --> 00:54:10,500
I’d rather not. I want to get some rest.

389
00:54:12,340 --> 00:54:13,540
Hold on!

390
00:54:18,940 --> 00:54:20,780
Have I done anything to upset you?

391
00:54:24,580 --> 00:54:26,140
No, why would you think that?

392
00:54:29,900 --> 00:54:30,740
I’m just afraid.

393
00:54:33,180 --> 00:54:33,980
Afraid?

394
00:54:36,140 --> 00:54:40,780
That you don’t feel the same way as I do, and you’re only doing this because you can’t refuse.

395
00:54:56,260 --> 00:54:58,260
I like you, Boss.

396
00:54:59,340 --> 00:55:01,100
I’ve liked you for a long time.

397
00:55:08,940 --> 00:55:13,140
You’ve liked me since when?

398
00:55:16,740 --> 00:55:17,540
I don’t know.

399
00:55:19,660 --> 00:55:22,060
But I think I’ve always liked you.

400
00:55:24,140 --> 00:55:30,340
You’re always nice to me, and yet I can’t help thinking that you like me too.

401
00:55:37,380 --> 00:55:38,460
But…

402
00:55:40,620 --> 00:55:43,380
what you want between us is impossible.

403
00:55:56,940 --> 00:56:02,140
Then, why don’t we make it possible?

404
00:56:05,740 --> 00:56:06,860
What do you mean?

405
00:56:08,980 --> 00:56:12,140
Can you be my girlfriend, Chonlada?

406
00:57:26,540 --> 00:57:28,500
Come here, girl.

407
00:57:31,900 --> 00:57:32,900
No, Dad.

408
00:57:34,140 --> 00:57:37,540
Why? It’s a welcome hug for my daughter-in-law.

409
00:57:38,740 --> 00:57:42,980
You told me she finally agreed to be your girlfriend. Come on then.

410
00:57:44,540 --> 00:57:45,860
I’ll squeeze till you scream.

411
00:57:46,660 --> 00:57:47,580
You can’t.

412
00:57:47,740 --> 00:57:52,700
You might be my dad, but don’t forget you’re also a man.

413
00:57:52,900 --> 00:57:56,540
Whatever you’ll do, please give Chonlada some respect.

414
00:57:56,980 --> 00:57:58,140
Wow,

415
00:57:58,700 --> 00:58:02,220
haven’t you two only started dating? You sure are very possessive.

416
00:58:03,740 --> 00:58:06,500
I was just teasing you.

417
00:58:06,780 --> 00:58:12,740
Don’t you remember? I used to teach you that we all have parents.

418
00:58:12,740 --> 00:58:16,300
Especially for the ladies, we must always treat them with respect.

419
00:58:19,780 --> 00:58:23,540
Welcome to the Watinwanich family.

420
00:58:24,700 --> 00:58:26,980
Now, you’re not only Nam’s lover,

421
00:58:28,580 --> 00:58:31,940
but you’re also one of our family.

422
00:58:33,860 --> 00:58:41,580
Wait, are you sure you didn’t imagine things that she finally said yes to be your girlfriend?

423
00:58:45,660 --> 00:58:46,460
Dad!

424
00:58:52,300 --> 00:58:57,660
Yes, Big Boss. Boss and I are now seeing each other.

425
00:59:01,060 --> 00:59:05,740
‘Big Boss’? You two are together now. You can call me ‘Dad’.

426
00:59:08,340 --> 00:59:11,380
Dad, don’t pressure her.

427
00:59:12,700 --> 00:59:17,860
Well, it’s just that we’re close now. But you two still address each other like that.

428
00:59:18,660 --> 00:59:20,780
Why do you have to be so formal?

429
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:23,340
Nam has never been in a relationship.

430
00:59:23,980 --> 00:59:28,420
So, she doesn’t know what the first rule of being a couple is, Uncle.

431
00:59:30,860 --> 00:59:31,740
What rule?

432
00:59:33,780 --> 00:59:37,140
Before you become a couple, you can address each other however you like.

433
00:59:37,500 --> 00:59:40,940
But once the status has changed, you have to change the way you call each other too.

434
00:59:46,980 --> 00:59:47,860
Mootoon (braised pork).

435
00:59:52,220 --> 00:59:58,580
Huh? Isn’t this Stir-fried Pork with Black Bean Sauce? It’s not braised pork.

436
00:59:59,340 --> 01:00:03,060
It’s Nam’s nickname when she was a kid.

437
01:00:04,340 --> 01:00:07,020
Back then, she was so chubby.

438
01:00:07,020 --> 01:00:12,180
Her face was so round that her mother often called her ‘Mootoon’.

439
01:00:14,340 --> 01:00:15,420
Dad…

440
01:00:18,900 --> 01:00:21,380
I was called ‘Ducky’ when I was little.

441
01:00:21,700 --> 01:00:24,540
Hmm? Do you like to eat duck?

442
01:00:25,060 --> 01:00:26,580
No, I was afraid of ducks.

443
01:00:26,580 --> 01:00:31,140
My dad called me Ducky so that if I kept hearing it, I wouldn’t be scared of it anymore.

444
01:00:33,500 --> 01:00:37,460
Then, you should call Nam ‘Palo’ (stewed in brown sauce).

445
01:00:37,460 --> 01:00:40,900
Because when she was little, she was afraid of Palo.

446
01:00:41,340 --> 01:00:42,980
Why Palo?

447
01:00:43,540 --> 01:00:44,780
Don’t you dare, Dad!

448
01:00:45,460 --> 01:00:46,700
- Go on, Uncle.
- Why?

449
01:00:47,780 --> 01:00:49,700
I think she must have heard it from somewhere.

450
01:00:50,540 --> 01:00:52,580
You see, Palo has brown or black sauce, right?

451
01:00:53,500 --> 01:00:58,340
She believed it’s that colour because there was a ghost in there.

452
01:00:58,340 --> 01:01:00,900
That’s why she’s scared of eating Palo.

453
01:01:03,700 --> 01:01:05,460
You’ve ruined everything, Dad.

454
01:01:08,100 --> 01:01:12,540
Are you still afraid of Palo ghost, Boss?

455
01:01:15,340 --> 01:01:16,900
Are you still afraid of ducks?

456
01:01:17,380 --> 01:01:18,820
Is that a retort?

457
01:01:23,660 --> 01:01:26,340
Oops, someone’s afraid of her girl.

458
01:01:29,340 --> 01:01:31,780
I’m not! Shush it.

459
01:01:32,100 --> 01:01:33,500
I was just kidding.

460
01:01:36,380 --> 01:01:43,340
Nam, I think Lada wants to eat some prawns. Peel them for her.

461
01:02:03,580 --> 01:02:05,860
’m about to peel it for you.

462
01:02:05,860 --> 01:02:07,300
Why are you peeling it too?

463
01:02:11,500 --> 01:02:16,420
So you won’t have to peel it alone from now on.

464
01:02:28,580 --> 01:02:29,540
Ouch, ants!

465
01:02:34,460 --> 01:02:35,980
Sweet, isn’t it?

466
01:02:36,580 --> 01:02:37,460
Yes.

467
01:02:48,700 --> 01:02:50,020
I have a question.

468
01:02:50,900 --> 01:02:54,340
If you have to be with me for the rest of your life, will you get bored of me?

469
01:02:55,900 --> 01:03:00,580
You weren’t listening at all, were you?

470
01:03:00,580 --> 01:03:02,140
To what Fah said during dinner.

471
01:03:02,340 --> 01:03:04,740
About you being scared of that Palo ghost?

472
01:03:04,780 --> 01:03:08,900
No, about me having you as my first lover.

473
01:03:14,140 --> 01:03:15,860
It’s such an honour indeed.

474
01:03:15,940 --> 01:03:20,700
I shall cherish and maintain this title as long as I can.

475
01:03:23,660 --> 01:03:28,660
So, should we do what Dad has suggested?

476
01:03:28,660 --> 01:03:30,220
Not the Palo ghost thing.

477
01:03:31,260 --> 01:03:34,180
You mean, our couple names?

478
01:03:36,540 --> 01:03:38,260
What do you want to call me then?

479
01:03:39,380 --> 01:03:40,860
What about you?

480
01:03:41,100 --> 01:03:42,940
I asked you first.

481
01:03:43,260 --> 01:03:44,300
You say it first.

482
01:03:47,300 --> 01:03:48,660
Are you embarrassed?

483
01:03:50,100 --> 01:03:52,780
Then, let’s not do it.

484
01:03:54,540 --> 01:03:57,620
But I want to call you with an endearing term too.

485
01:04:00,300 --> 01:04:01,700
I have an idea.

486
01:04:11,860 --> 01:04:13,260
You want me to write on your back?

487
01:04:13,260 --> 01:04:16,860
Yes. You do it for me and I’ll do it for you.

488
01:04:18,180 --> 01:04:18,980
Okay.

489
01:04:25,860 --> 01:04:26,660
Done.

490
01:04:28,940 --> 01:04:29,900
My turn now.

491
01:04:41,380 --> 01:04:42,580
Is it ticklish?

492
01:04:44,180 --> 01:04:44,980
No.

493
01:04:48,740 --> 01:04:49,540
Is that it?

494
01:04:50,780 --> 01:04:53,180
Mhm. Can you guess what I wrote?

495
01:04:59,100 --> 01:04:59,900
Lada.

496
01:05:05,060 --> 01:05:09,460
Huh? Why so quiet? Did I get it wrong?

497
01:05:11,300 --> 01:05:18,700
Or do you want me to call you ‘my dear Lada’?

498
01:05:22,140 --> 01:05:23,580
‘Lada’ is right.

499
01:05:24,500 --> 01:05:31,380
I just never thought you calling my name like that would make me feel so complete.

500
01:05:33,460 --> 01:05:37,580
But earlier, you still called me Boss.

501
01:05:38,940 --> 01:05:44,140
Or is it because you didn’t know what I wrote?

502
01:05:45,140 --> 01:05:46,940
Nam.

503
01:05:57,740 --> 01:06:01,820
Do you not like it? Or did I get it wrong?

504
01:06:02,060 --> 01:06:04,100
Do you want me to use other terms instead?

505
01:06:04,980 --> 01:06:07,340
Or should I just call you Boss like before?

506
01:06:15,100 --> 01:06:18,620
When I saw Din and Rose together at first,

507
01:06:18,620 --> 01:06:23,340
I never understood why they must be so clingy to each other all the time.

508
01:06:25,420 --> 01:06:26,900
Now I know why.

509
01:06:30,260 --> 01:06:38,780
I have no problem at all, but can we use those terms only after work hours?

510
01:06:43,100 --> 01:06:45,780
Are you afraid people might find out we’re together?

511
01:06:46,740 --> 01:06:51,940
It’s not that. I just don’t want your staff to question your authority, Boss.

512
01:06:56,740 --> 01:06:58,140
I mean, Nam.

513
01:07:02,340 --> 01:07:03,140
Sure.

514
01:07:05,060 --> 01:07:07,380
But you must give me something in return.

515
01:07:08,060 --> 01:07:09,500
What do you want?

516
01:07:11,380 --> 01:07:12,180
Well…

517
01:07:17,380 --> 01:07:18,620
Hey!

518
01:07:18,740 --> 01:07:19,540
What?

519
01:07:21,740 --> 01:07:25,060
Well, just call me that.

520
01:07:25,060 --> 01:07:29,900
Then, you have to call me by that name every time too. Okay?

521
01:07:32,780 --> 01:07:38,260
Of course. Even if you don’t ask, I’m going to do it anyway.

522
01:07:39,820 --> 01:07:43,660
We might be seeing each other secretly, but at least

523
01:07:43,940 --> 01:07:48,260
you should always remember that I’m no longer your boss.

524
01:07:49,340 --> 01:07:51,260
It’s you who’s the boss from now on.

525
01:07:55,180 --> 01:07:58,340
Please be nice to me, Boss.

526
01:08:01,860 --> 01:08:02,980
Sure.

527
01:08:04,540 --> 01:08:05,900
It’s your day off tomorrow.

528
01:08:07,140 --> 01:08:08,740
Do you have any plans?

529
01:08:12,100 --> 01:08:15,940
I’m thinking of going home in Bangkok. There’re still things I have to take care of.

530
01:08:20,740 --> 01:08:21,540
How will you get there?

531
01:08:22,100 --> 01:08:23,420
Do you need a ride?

532
01:08:26,140 --> 01:08:30,779
Isn’t it nice to have a girlfriend? I even have a personal driver too.

533
01:08:32,300 --> 01:08:36,180
But it’s all right.

534
01:08:38,140 --> 01:08:40,580
I can go by myself. Don’t worry.

535
01:08:43,939 --> 01:08:48,540
Well, if you need a ride, you can always let me know.

536
01:08:48,540 --> 01:08:50,300
It’s not a bother at all.

537
01:08:50,340 --> 01:08:51,140
Yes, sir.

538
01:08:53,100 --> 01:08:54,380
Remember what Dad told you earlier?

539
01:08:56,140 --> 01:08:58,700
That you’re not just my lover.

540
01:08:59,060 --> 01:09:01,260
But you’re also one of my family.

541
01:09:02,859 --> 01:09:08,380
I also want to visit your parents and pay them respect too.

542
01:09:09,380 --> 01:09:11,420
I want to be a part of your family.

543
01:09:16,380 --> 01:09:17,180
Of course.

544
01:09:24,979 --> 01:09:25,779
Cold, isn’t it?

545
01:09:29,540 --> 01:09:30,340
You’re cold?

546
01:09:30,660 --> 01:09:32,700
Mhm. Aren’t you cold?

547
01:09:33,939 --> 01:09:36,899
Free hug. Satisfaction guaranteed or a full hug back.

548
01:09:36,899 --> 01:09:37,979
Come here.

549
01:10:06,740 --> 01:10:10,580
[Next Episode]
Who do you think make my company in this f***ing red?!

550
01:10:10,580 --> 01:10:14,620
Lada, your job is to make Kirk love you

551
01:10:14,620 --> 01:10:16,580
and propose to you for a marriage.

552
01:10:16,580 --> 01:10:19,180
Your family still doesn't accept me, does they?

553
01:10:19,500 --> 01:10:22,980
What if our relationship has come to a dead end?

554
01:10:23,580 --> 01:10:25,420
I’ll do everything

555
01:10:25,420 --> 01:10:28,820
and will never let you face the problems alone.

556
01:10:28,820 --> 01:10:30,780
Congratulations.

557
01:10:30,780 --> 01:10:33,740
And sorry about Chonlada.

558
01:10:34,340 --> 01:10:35,900
Is there something wrong with her?

559
01:10:40,740 --> 01:10:44,300
You’d better hurry and have a grandson for me.

560
01:11:06,860 --> 01:11:12,380
♫ Since the day you came into my life, I start to realise…♫

561
01:11:12,380 --> 01:11:16,540
♫ What it’s like to be someone who matters ♫

562
01:11:16,540 --> 01:11:22,500
♫ Feeling so warm whenever I see you♫

563
01:11:22,500 --> 01:11:25,260
♫ Who often stays close to me♫

564
01:11:25,260 --> 01:11:30,140
♫ I just want you to know♫

565
01:11:30,140 --> 01:11:36,980
♫ This feeling that’s happening inside♫

566
01:11:36,980 --> 01:11:40,060
♫ I don’t want to hide it anymore♫

567
01:11:40,060 --> 01:11:43,780
♫ I guess I’ll have to tell you♫

568
01:11:44,460 --> 01:11:48,500
♫ You’re the one that change my life ♫

569
01:11:49,220 --> 01:11:53,500
♫ Make me feel more important than anyone♫

570
01:11:53,500 --> 01:11:58,820
♫ Thank you so much for making my life meaningful♫

571
01:11:58,820 --> 01:12:05,140
♫ How lucky I am to have you♫

572
01:12:09,340 --> 01:12:15,140
[Waves of Deception]

